properties.name: Product Design
properties.definition:
Generic Definitions:
1. [Wikipedia]: A design is a plan or specification for the construction of an object or system or for the implementation of an activity or process, or the result of that plan or specification in the form of a prototype, product or process. 

2. [ISO 14813-5]: How parts or constituents are related to an organised whole, providing specification for the structure, organization, appearance, etc., of a system or entity.

Product-centric Definitions:
3. [ISO 10795]: Set of information that defines the characteristics of a product. 

5. [ISO 3834-1]: Set of requirements for a product specified by customers, by the organization in anticipation of customer requirements, or by regulation. 

Note 1 to entry: The requirements for products and in some cases associated processes can be contained in, for example, technical specifications, product standards, process standards, contractual agreements and regulatory requirements.

Software-centric Definition:
6. [Rational Unified Process (in software development)]: A software requirements specification (SRS) is a technical document that describes in detail the externally visible characteristics of a software product.   A Software Design Specification then outlines an implementation that shows how the system satisfies the requirements of the SRS.

properties.name: Task Description
properties.comment:
1. A task description can be created, assigned and detailed electronically in some project or other task management system, verbally communicated, self-assigned and recorded in one's mobile phone, or post-it note, or kept "in the back of one's mind."

2. The term is is asserted under plan specification since one can argue that a task specification also implies (or sets some expectation at a minimum) some objective or outcome to be accomplished.

3. A task may be, but is not required to be, part of a work breakdown structure or action complex.

4. We leave out that a task definition is not broken down further. In decomposing projects, complex tasks are decomposed (involving a work-breakdown structure) until they are "simple enough" to be assignable to a given person or group of persons, in which they are able to be performed and completed in a narrow time frame.
properties.definition:
A task specification prescribes some action intended to be assigned to and performed by some person or group of persons, that specifies or sets some expecation as to the timeframe in which it is to occur.

Task description =def. an objective specification that prescribes some task that is intended to be concretized by a specific person or group of persons, and which specifies some starting or ending timeframe in which the task is to occur.

First Order Logic Definition: 

instance-of(x, action, t) ≡ ∃y (instance-of(y, agent, t) & has-agent (x, y, t))

instance-of(x, action, t) → ∃y, t′(instance-of(y, intention, t′) & realizes (x, y) & (precedes(t′, t) ˅ first-instant(t′, t)))

properties.comment:
When concretized, may be realized in a process performed by some agent to achieve the prescribed process endpoints by taking the prescribed actions.
Like all IAO: information content entities, a Plan Specification 'g-depends on at some time' various types Information Bearing Entities, such as on paper, in a database, on some email server, or even in the working memory of some autonomous computer application. properties.name: Task Description
properties.comment:
1. A task description can be created, assigned and detailed electronically in some project or other task management system, verbally communicated, self-assigned and recorded in one's mobile phone, or post-it note, or kept "in the back of one's mind."

2. The term is is asserted under plan specification since one can argue that a task specification also implies (or sets some expectation at a minimum) some objective or outcome to be accomplished.

3. A task may be, but is not required to be, part of a work breakdown structure or action complex.

4. We leave out that a task definition is not broken down further. In decomposing projects, complex tasks are decomposed (involving a work-breakdown structure) until they are "simple enough" to be assignable to a given person or group of persons, in which they are able to be performed and completed in a narrow time frame.
properties.definition:
A task specification prescribes some action intended to be assigned to and performed by some person or group of persons, that specifies or sets some expecation as to the timeframe in which it is to occur.

Task description =def. an objective specification that prescribes some task that is intended to be concretized by a specific person or group of persons, and which specifies some starting or ending timeframe in which the task is to occur.
